The theory provides many testable predictions.  The proposed research will characterize superconducting samples with respect to these theoretical predictions.  Each of the predictions requires making a characterization of bulk superconductor behavior that has not been previously reported.  Consequently, not only will the proposed research produce several experimental tests of the hole theory of superconductivity, it will also contribute previously unmeasured superconductor characteristics to the existing body of knowledge.
\\
